```
stop running python
>>> quit()

## switch drive from C to D 
C:\Users\User>D:

D:\>

## go into existing forlder with cd
D:\>cd ExistingFolder
D:\ExistingFolder\>

 go back to the upper folder
D:\ExistingFolder\>cd\
D:\>

// make a new directory or folder
D:\>mkdir PythonFolder

// go to the folder
D:\>cd Python1

// open youre favorite editor, in this case ATOM
D:\Python1>atom

// run the programm from your command line and get the result
D:\Python1>python HelloWorld.py
HelloWorld
```

